Text:
@wideawake_media I did, and the answer is zero to each question, because we were too busy leading active lives and enthusiastic about learning;
ie:
NOT addicted to social media, vacuous ‘influencers’ or screen based gaming;
and NOT listening to media &amp; official claptrap about ‘mental health’.

@Alteffour69 @AshIyne @ColSandersNZ @RadioGenoa You are exactly why Americans shouldnt be allowed social media accounts.

Obvious mental health issues and nowhere near enough brain cells rattling around your head to be trusted.

You are precisely why the stereotypes about your country exist.

@DaisyIsNotHere Social media is not good for mental health.

Especially when you are being personally open &amp; honest about a contentious social issue. You become an avatar for others to latch onto.

Hope you feel better!
